    drainagePara: "Monsoon flash floods undermine lot grading in hours and proper lot slope away from the slab plus HOA retention basin integrity is the primary defense. Phoenix HOAs through Sun City, Sun Lakes, and Anthem enforce retention basin maintenance that directly affects adjacent foundation moisture. Water-harvesting landscape conversions under the Salt River Project and City of Phoenix rebate programs change moisture patterns around slabs, and reputable crews audit irrigation patterns before and after any conversion to catch emerging issues.",
    seasonalPara: "October through April produces mild temperatures and dry soil, the working window for Phoenix foundation repair. June through September extreme heat and monsoon thunderstorms make both pouring and excavation unsafe, and reputable crews refuse to pour after 9 am from late May through mid-September. Pier installation continues year-round because the activity generates less heat exposure than slab pouring, but pre-dawn starts are standard July through August to meet OSHA heat-illness prevention rules.",
    localDisasterPara: "The 2023 record summer heat dome with multiple 115F-plus days caused widespread slab curling and plastic-shrinkage cracking on noon pours, and Valley Building Inspector data tracks the callback surge that followed. Monsoon 2022 and haboob events drove flash-flood undermining of retention-basin-adjacent slabs in Summerlin and Anthem. The Salt River flood of 1891 remains the documented historic baseline that shapes floodplain regulation across the lower Valley.",
